I could peel you like a pear, and God himself would call it justice.
I will die sometime soon.
One day I'll duck too slow, and at westminster, they'll sing out "long live the king" for someone else.
I beg you, let it be a son of mine.
I am not moved to tears.
I have no sons. You have too many sons. You don't need more.
