Ladies and gentlemen, this is Harry Esterbrook speaking to you from the courthouse here in Hillsboro, where the jury has returned to render its verdict in the historic Hillsboro monkey trial case.
The judge has taken the bench, in a few moments, we will know whether Bertram Cates will be found innocent or guilty.
I wish I could describe the tension, in this courtroom today,
The verbal and legal elements-- one moment, please.
Please stand by.
I've been on the phone with the lieutenant governor all morning.
The newspapers haven't been very kind to us.
