Cut them all into one!
Get the ropes!
I'll show you!
There you have it.
Where love led the Bishop of Hennau, and about the soliloquy of madmen.
Get her!
Concubine!
Alexandra!
They did quite a job on you, the beasts!
There's not enough for two, but have some...
Never mind.
You wouldn't have a pinch of salt, would you?
Smells good.
We defend ourselves in need like she-bears, but at other times we attack our loved ones like lynxes!
Why do you appeal to God?
They made a lout into a lord.
Did you hear the captain?
Get up! Let's go find shelter.
They invited me to supper in a monastery.
It was Easter. Whores of Herod!
Stupid mercenaries.
To cast out a beggar...
What was it called?
The monastery was on Turnov Road.
Don't you know it?
Suddenly it was full of soldiers. I was hungry.
But the captain!
Cornets... Drums...
Bad farmers clear woods.
Bad kings start wars.
You're all pagans.
Hear that? What...
They tried to kill me in a pub in Boleslav!
What henchmen they were!
Stop staring!
Hear me?
Christ! Savior!
Holy Virgin!
Give him some water.
He didn't rob or steal.
His head was cracked in two.
He just put loam on his wound and rode home!
- The gallows await him.
- You mean the axe!
Noble blood gets the sword.
On the fate of men and the lot of widows.
Lady Katerina!
Lord Mikoléé!
Praise be to God, at least you are here!
Come and rest!
We don't have that horse anymore...
- I didn't expect...
- Do you know about...
What about Jifi?
- And Burjan?
- Did you see mine?
Yes, I did.
- Eat this.
- Are you fishing?
Whatever the flood brings.
I'd sell some in Boleslav
- What are you thinking of?
- We won't get in without wares.
- Why Boleslav?
- Is he alive?
- He's no use to us otherwise.
- I know what Kozlik would order.
We'll bring a basket of fish
We'll be like farmers, and we'll charge the prison
He'd tell you to hide from the King's wrath, and return later to rebuild Rohééek.
Attack the prison with stones? The two of us?
A single wolf can defeat a pack of dogs if the time is right.
We'll storm Boleslav!
Shut up and fish.
We would need a regiment!
Kozlik is dead.
If not, he will get the axe.
No power can drag him from death but God's.
- Then God will guide us.
- He sinned like a soldiers.
Wish him a peaceful death to pay for his sins.
Do you want the executioner to take him?
We are both old and we await death.
You protect yourselves and your progeny.
Allow the aged a peaceful grave.
Remember the living!
Spring shall pass, and soon we shall sow.
Keep going along this road.
Go home.
I took you from Oboist against your will
No one will reproach you.
Go.
Go. Cheer up Lazar and wait.
I know what happened, and that you are sad.
I know you love me, but we must save Kozlik from dishonor.
Your names are signed in hell. Be damned!
- Don't blaspheme!
- May you never know peace!
Shut up! Don't invoke God.
He I hear you. .
Their time had come.
Kozlik woke me and said,
"Take the arrows. "
I followed him.
It was pitch dark.
They called to each other.
When their time comes, they battle for a mate.
- To overcome her?
- No, a mate calls his mate.
- And she?
- She submits to the stronger.
- Forever?
- Yes.
- Only people know that...
- And the defeated?
He must have known our scent.
Kozlik wouldn't let me shoot him
- Why is he called the "Goat?"
- We've always called him that.
Once he beat me until I bled.
What happened then?
His antlers were bigger than branches.
He looked at us without fear.
Kozlik motioned for silence. We went closer.
It moved away, and we went after it.
Below the hillside there was a bare plain.
Grass, stones, lichen...
This valley was more wretched than a cemetery.
Bones, limbs, a thousand antlers on white skulls.
He stood alone in the middle. Defeated, alone.
Alone.
Kozlik whispered, "Look... "
"The solitude of death. "
He raised his antlers, and called.
- Who did he call...
- Shh!
Just a moment longer.
Take Alexandra with you.
Your thoughts stray to a place where punishment waits.
- What about me?
- We haven't given up yet.
I will be judged over and over, even if I am punished.
Do not talk of punishment, and prepare the wedding.
My brothers will bring you a message from me.
God made me love you.
You are my wife.
Alexandra!
Alexandra!
Just a moment more.
Welcome...
You are...
Send her back! Go away!
Get out!
This is not the time to return.
- What are you doing here?
- I came...
He sent you. You could've come long ago, but you liked to sin!
- You're his concubine!
- No!
Look!
I cannot watch you writhe in pus.
- I didn't abandon my will.
- Really?
Who defended me?
So, you come with reproach instead of repentance?
I came so you could judge me.
Do not judge, and you will not be judged.
Ask God for more humility.
I have not heard you renounce him yet.
Go! You broke the vow I made to God!
You are not even fit to feed the swine!
You'll be back. Trust me
The pain will subside.
The torture will pass.
I'll speak for you when the time is right.
Wait! you were my guiding light...
Do not abandon me, Lord...
Remember not my sins, but remember me by your mercy...
My parents have left me, but your hand welcomes me... for my wrongs have risen above my head like a stone...
I cannot bear them...
You measured the days, nothing lies before You.
It is nothing more than vanity for every man...
Man is transient as a shadow...
He hurries in vain...
He gathers and knows not who takes...
Judge me, Lord. I abide and hope in Your sincerity...
Try me, burn my loins and heart...
The suffering of my heart becomes greater...
Lead me from my anguish...
Teach me about your path...
Lead me to those who guard me...
Do not give me to the desires of my enemies...
For he who breathes cruelty should stand against me...
Do not unite my soul with the sinful...
... and the murderous man of my life...
... and the murderous...
... and the murderous man of my life...
In his hands is ignobleness...
His right hand is full of spoils...
Extend Your hand from on high...
Thunder crashes, burning coals fall on him...
Throw him on the fire...
Into a deep pit...
So he can no longer stand.
Remember your mercy, Lord...
Remember your mercy, Lord...
... and the charity you have shown through the ages...
See my suffering and wretchedness...
... and stay close to me...
Your hand presses down heavily on me...
Take your rod away from me...
From your blows I perished...
My heart has melted like wax inside me...
My strength is parched, and my tongue clings to my mouth...
For you have placed me in the dust of death...
For you have placed me in the dust of death...
My wounds have festered... for my foolishness...
Lead me in Your justice from those who watch over me for there is no sincerity in their words.
Let them fall from their counsel. Help me.
For who will celebrate
Your name in the grave?
Extend Your hand from on high...
Thunder crashes.
Burning coals fall on him.
Marketa, daughter of Lazar, do you take Mikoléé, son of Kozlik, as your husband?
I do!
Mikolaé, do you take
Marketa, daughter of Lazar...
I bind your hands with the sanctity of matrimony.
What God hath joined, let no man tear asunder.
Let's go!
You were my dearest...
What have we here? Greetings.
Just in time.
You'll find something better
Stand still!
It was mournful at Oboist
Stand still!
I found her, starving...
What are you doing here?
Come on, dear lass.
Let us three wander together.
The Lord will provide shelter
We'll have a merry winter.
Marketa, wait.
Little one!
Stop, I say! Marketa...
Where are you going?
Wait!
Marketa...
Is that all the thanks
I get for saving your life?
Stop!
Marketa...
Stop, you rascal!
Wait, Marketa!
After some time Marketa bore a son named Vaclav.
Alexandra also gave birth, and Marketa nursed both babies.
They grew up to be fine boys, but love and certainty fought against cruelty and doubt for their souls.
