He'll see the queen's quarters are made ready to her.
Stay where you are.
- Have I dismissed you?
- No, Your Majesty.
This is my palace, Caesar.
All of it is available to me at my will.
I am not your prisoner.
If anything, you are my guest.
Most kind.
And as for having my quarters, as you put it, made ready... my chief handmaiden has, by now, brought the others out of hiding.
They should almost be finished.
Impossible.
The doors are under guard.
There are doors, and doors.
Oh, yes. Of course.
