Kujuro!
A lovely visitor.
Kujuro.
I brought the plans.
Thanks. I'll get leave to go home tomorrow, and be back in three days.
I struggled to get it for you.
So please be back in three days.
I'm sorry to cause you trouble.
You know I'm Tawaraboshi?
Alone, Yasubei?
I know you. That mask's no good.
I expected 5 or 6 men.
But then I might have had to die.
Is that why you came alone?
You've fallen into my trap.
What trap?
I'm not working for Uesugi.
But I knew the rumor would bring you to my school to fight.
Or to get me drunk and kill me.
You came, as I thought.
And now I know what I wanted to know.
Don't talk nonsense.
I attacked you for criticizing the Asano men.
Is that right? I don't think so.
Yasubei, when is it?
When is what?
Oh, that's right. You can't talk.
But I think of you as a friend.
So if you take a long trip, or a new lord, stop by my school.
We'll have a farewell drink.
Yasubei!
Don't be suspicious of me.
Welcome.
Steward Obana will stay the night.
Show every respect.
Forgive me. Your arrival was not expected. We will make ready.
IMPERIAL ENVOY: MITSUTADA OBANA
Thank you for staying with us.
My journey is on behalf of
Prince Seikanji.
We are taking his offerings to Zojoji Temple.
I see. The Prince stayed at this inn last spring.
Remember, when Lord Asano drew his sword in the Castle.
Yes, of course.
Were you accompanying him then?
You were? I'm the son-in-law here.
Sorry I was too busy to see to you.
I have the list of offerings.
As innkeeper, you have to report these things, don't you?
Please study it well.
LORD ASANO'S CREST
Say, listen. Get out, quick!
What's wrong?
Otoki, don't get excited.
Don't sit down. Where'd it go?
Who?
Not him, it. Where is it? Where?
What?
You know, that!
There'd have been advance warning if Steward Obana was coming.
Say Officer Koga wishes to see him.
No, Officer Koga.
Why? I have doubts, so I'll check.
If he's an imposter, you'll be an accomplice.
No, it's no mistake.
He's Steward Obana.
Well, you would know.
Actually, checking was an excuse.
I wanted to thank him for being so kind when he was here last year.
Just let me in for a minute.
No, he's not the same.
What do you mean?
He's here on behalf of the Prince this time.
He's in a high position, so you can't see him.
Do you have proof?
Proof? The proof is this.
Show due respect. Bow!
The Prince's own handwriting.
Last year I asked him for some, to have as our household treasure.
Today I received this from Steward Obana.
This is your proof. Study it.
Yes, without a doubt.
Hanbei, I thank you.
Take this. You may need it again at the Hakone guardpost.
SEIKANJI FAMILY STEWARD
MITSUTADA OBANA'S LODGINGS
You're strange today.
No, what I did was right.
Remember Otoki, our guest's name is Steward Obana. Understand?
Yes, I've begun to believe it too.
OYAMA-YA INN
What Okano got for us is priceless.
A new storehouse with a passage underground out to a vacant lot.
We must be careful here.
Father!
If those Dutchmen knew, would they think we're doing the right thing?
I see. That's how you young people think.
That's not all we think about.
But our willingness to die for a just cause is the same as yours.
Takada.
Seems our time is approaching.
