Warms you up inside.
Poor hospitality, living as I do now.
Ume, serve him more.
Thank you.
By the way, what brought you to Edo so suddenly?
Actually, I came to bid my lady farewell.
Farewell?
It's not just me. We've all been masterless samurai too long.
We're tired of being so poor that we're nearly starving.
But no lord will employ us.
So I've decided to settle down in Yamashina and become a farmer.
Chamberlain!
Some of the men say we should go and avenge our lord.
But it's only the voice of their desperation.
Or their miserable attempt to succeed by attracting attention.
Kuranosuke.
You really mean to retire to Yamashina?
Yes, my lady.
How could your samurai spirit allow you to?
If I closed my eyes to reality and led a raid on Kira's mansion...
I would have popular approval.
But the world is not so simple.
I understand.
Till today I believed there were still true samurai among you.
That is why I lived on in a world that holds no meaning for me.
I must pray for my dead husband.
I bid you farewell.
Please wait, my lady.
For the last time, may I offer incense at my lord's memorial?
No, you may not.
I do not refuse for my own sake.
The prayers of a person like you would not please our late lord.
