Gentlemen, we are wasting time.
I've been making a few rough calculations based on the effect of two 20-megaton bombs dropped on New York City in the middle of a normal workday.
I estimate the immediate dead at about three million.
I include in this figure those buried beneath the collapsed buildings.
Wouldn't make any difference,
Admiral Wilcox, whether they reached a shelter or not.
They would die just the same.
Add another million or two who'll die within about five weeks.
