THE END
 In the beginning was the Word,
and the Word was with God,
and the Word was God.
 I am He.
He was in the beginning with God,.
All things were made through him,
and without him was made nothing
that has been made.
In him was life,
and the life was the light of men.
And the light shines on in the darkness,
and the darkness grasped it not.
The greatest story ever told.
You have been asking questions about a child.
We have, Your Majesty. We've come a great distance in search of him.
And who told you about such a child who is to be born a king in my kingdom?
We saw the rising of his star, and his star has been our guide.
You have followed a star from Asia to the centre of the world?
Aben?
Do you know of this child king they look for?
In prophecy there is mention made of a Messiah.
And where is this Messiah to be born?
The prophet Hosea named
Egypt as the place of birth.
The great Isaiah spoke of Nazareth.
That was 700 years ago.
Your Majesty, if I may be so bold, the prophet Michaeus named Bethlehem.
I remember.
"From you, Bethlehem, shall he come forth who is to be ruler in all Israel."
I am an Idumean, not a Judean.
The priests here in Judea mock me in their temple.
The temple which I built.
They accuse me of impiety.
Tell them, Antipas.
The priests are envious of my father.
He knows the prophets better, and has more faith in them.
Everyone knows that I am a pious man.
Magi, when you find this child, how can you be certain that he is the one?
By the accuracy of the stars.
Yes.
Then it is only by the star that you can know.
What greater spokesman can a child have than a star?
The air is cold. Your Majesty should rest.
If great Herod will give us leave, we should be on our way.
Go then.
If you find this child, bring me word, that I, too, might worship him.
Follow them and keep me informed.
 He shall be great...
and called the Son of the Most High.
And the Lord God will give him
the throne of his ancestor, David.
And his kingdom shall know no end.
Who are you?
We have come from a far land to see your child.
What will you name him?
Jesus.
Jesus will be his name.
I bring gold, for the sovereignty of our king.
And frankincense, for the worship of God.
And myrrh, for preservation until time everlasting.
The old king.
We leave at once.
 Take the child. Flee.
The stars foretold that one day I would be king.
- And I am king.
- Truly.
If there is anything in prophecy, surely it is not the stars, but God who has sent...
Huh! God! Where is God?
Or the child of God, except in man's most dangerous imagination?
The child of imagination is the child I fear.
And, my son, when you reign - if you do - remember that.
- Well?
- Sire.
We followed them.
They went to Bethlehem.
Bethlehem.
In fulfilment of your prophecy.
Prophecies have been scattered through history like seed. You can disregard this.
Or find one more fitting.
As I remember
"A voice was heard in Bethlehem, weeping and mourning."
"A voice was heard in Ramah."
Bethlehem...
"There was weeping and great mourning."
"It was Rachel, weeping for her children, because they were no more."
Let this be the prophecy fulfilled.
Go to Bethlehem and kill this child.
To be sure, every newborn boy in Bethlehem must die.
Be certain that none escape.
You have a question?
Then go!
Sire.
Not one is alive.
"For unto us a child is born, unto us a son is given; and his name shall be called Wonderful,
Everlasting Father, the Prince of Peace."
King Herod is dead!
King Herod is dead at last!
These travellers have just brought the news from Jerusalem.
Herod is dead!
Home.
Nazareth.
The old Herod is dead.
Death to the new one. Long live Israel!
How far is the nearest Roman legion?
Three days' march, sire. In Syria.
Send a messenger there, to the Roman governor.
Inform him... inform him that the eagle of Rome has been torn down and desecrated by a Jerusalem mob.
Send us the Deliverer, the Messiah.
Send us the Promised One.
Let these men be an example to all who challenge the peace of Rome.
I will call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised, and so shall I be saved from mine enemies.
He shall judge thy people with righteousness, and thy poor with judgment.
The mountains shall bring peace to the people, and the little hills...
Greetings, in the name of Augustus Caesar.
Caesar will not regret what he has done for the son of his old friend, King Herod.
What is that?
In time of trouble, the people pray for one to save them, a deliverer.
Your father kept the people in order.
In this you have failed.
I must inform you that we will take over.
My father's kingdom was guaranteed by Caesar.
From now on, a Roman legion, directed by a Roman governor, will govern Judea.
- You are the High Priest?
- As you see.
Shemiah, in the vestments of the High Priest.
From now on, those vestments will stay in my headquarters, and those who defy us will not be allowed to wear them.
Hear my cry, O God, attend unto my prayer; from the end of the earth will I cry unto thee.
Lead me to the rock that is higher than l; for thou hast been a shelter for me, and a strong tower from the enemy.
I wait for the Lord, my soul doth wait,
and in his word do I hope.
My God, my God,
why hast thou forsaken me?
Why are thou so far from helping me?
O my God, I cry in the daytime,
but thou hearest not,.
And in the night season,
and am not silent.
Our fathers trusted in thee,.
They trusted, and thou didst deliver them.
They cried unto thee, and were delivered,.
They trusted in thee,
and were not confounded.
In thee, O Lord, do I put my trust,.
Deliver me in they righteousness.
Judge me, O God, and plead my cause against the ungodly nation;
O deliver me from the deceitful and unjust men.
For thou art the God of my strength.
Tomorrow a Roman escort will see you across the Jordan to your father's palace.
Jordan and Galilee will be your tetrarchy.
O send out thy light and thy truth; let them lead me.
