Do not labour for the food that perishes, but for that which endures - the food of eternal life.
For the bread of God is that which comes from heaven and gives life to the world.
And everyone who eats of this bread will live for ever.
Therefore, put away all anxious thoughts about food to keep you alive, clothes to cover your body.
Life is more than food, and the body more than clothing.
Think of the ravens.
They neither sow nor reap.
They have no storehouse nor barn.
Yet God feeds them.
And how much more are you worth than birds?
Is there a man among you who by worry can add one minute to his span of life?
If you cannot do so small a thing, why do you worry about your other needs?
O you men of little faith.
Do not set your heart on what you eat or drink.
These are things that all the others in the world run after.
You have a Father who knows that you need them.
Set your mind upon his kingdom, and all of these things shall be yours, without the asking.
Tell us, when will the Kingdom of God come?
The Kingdom of God is here, within you.
A thief has stolen my coat.
Is that all, Peter?
Is that all?! It was the only coat I had.
But of what value is a thing which can be stolen by a thief?
