Give him your cloak also.
And give him anything else he wishes within your power to give him, for he is poor in spirit, and in need.
But if everyone did what you say, thieves would soon take over the world.
Thieves and murderers walk in darkness.
You must be their light, Peter, not their judge.
All I'm saying is, someone has taken my coat.
I think he was wrong to take it.
All I'm saying, Peter, is that as you have been judging, you will be judged.
And with your measure, it will be measured to you.
It was the best coat I ever owned.
