We're supposed to be comrades, our lives all pledged to the same cause.
Thank you very much.
Come back again!
Please come again.
Sir, the baggage. Here you go, sir.
What's wrong?
I apologize for the disarray, sir.
I'm sorry to barge in like this.
- May I ask who you are?
- Sir, I may not look like it, but...
...thanks to our generous patrons,
I am the manager of Sagamiya.
What do they call you?
Your name.
Sir, my name is Okiku.
There's no doubt that he's a ronin, originally from Bishu?
Well, at least that's what he claims.
Nobody has confirmed it yet.
So, he lives in a mud hut by the Kamakura riverbed works as a bouncer... a hired body- guard, and extorts and blackmails?
He's a ruffian, indeed!
Yes, sir.
Perhaps I got carried away about increasing our manpower.
Seems I've hired someone we ought to suspect.
